reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, Good Size & Easy to Assemble
reviews.reviewText: The instructions were a bit confusing at first because some of the parts didn’t have the correct stickers, but once I figured that out it only took me about an hour total to put together. It wasn’t that hardI wanted a taller shoe rack to kind of double as a table in my closet and this is PERFECT! :)It’s actually pretty sturdy, and you could definitely put two side by side if you needed that much storage.I may buy a few more of these for my house entryway 10/10 happy with my purchase

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Thought it was a wider
reviews.reviewText: Love the wooden shelf. Its pretty tall. Wish it was wider. Right now can only hold about 4 pairs across each shelf. This thing is sturdy. Easy to build. And i mean easy. Sleek and nice. It looks better than those low to the ground plastic ones for sure. Looks exactly how it is in the picture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Couple of kinks but the end result is great!
reviews.reviewText: The shelf came decently packaged. There was no bag to hold the 34 screws, so they were scattered all around the packaging. There were 35 total screws included with this order. Ease of putting together was nice. I was able to put it together in about 30 minutes. A couple of the holes for the screws did not poke all the way through, however the Allen wrench that was provided was able to fix that problem pretty quickly by just sticking it through the holes with some force. One side of the rack had one screw hole that did not have the screw seat to screw into, so it just wobbles in the hole, but I am still able to keep the rack secure enough for use. End product looks great, and I really like the wooden top. I am satisfied!

reviews.reviewText: Very easy to put together and seems very sturdy. I love the shelf on top, I can put my purse and my fiance's lunchbox there.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stable. Holds shoes.
reviews.reviewText: Just assembled this rack and I am pleased. It matches the description and feels sturdy, even after I filled it with shoes.
